        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          It's difficult to say "we deserved to win", because the difference in overall play wasn't a 3-point difference, but we deserved at least a draw whereas Liverpool deserved a draw at best. I'll just leave it at that. Unexpectedly, we dominated possession and heavily (61% in terms of time with the ball- which gave Liverpool their lowest recording of the season, this a team who edged best-in-Europe Man City 52%-48%). Our press at times resembled the 4-2-4 which Roger Schmidt employed at Leverkusen and with Oezil advanced, we forced a lot of errors from a team who are comfortable with the ball. It is strange to see a Juergen Klopp team 'out-pressed' (for want of a better term) but he was specifically out-German-pressed. Both Torreira (MotM) and Xhaka were excellent whereas Wijnaldum was poor and Fabinho was terrible. Milner played very well but the midfield battle was comfortably won by Arsenal.....

        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          .. Leno did nothing wrong for Liverpool's goal. He couldn't risk catching the ball and obviously couldn't see behind him. It only bounced into Milner's path because of the deflection off of Rob Holding. Awarding that an error is harsh in the extreme. Had he left it, he would have been criticised so it's damned if you do and damned if you don't in that situation. I'm not sure what he was doing coming out towards van Dijk, which almost gifted Liverpool a goal, though. I'm all for GKs commanding the box but there was absolutely no need to engage the ball in that situation. He did make up for it with two decent saves from van Dijk though and he is so comfortable with the ball at his feet, Liverpool's front 3 backed off on many an occasion- something which would not have happened with Cech between the sticks. All in all, a point against a genuine title contender is a good one. You know your team are improving when you're slightly down about having not beaten a CL finalist.

        • [ - ] Castle - member since 08-Sep-15

          I think a draw were quite justified result but a scoreline should have been much bigger. Way better performance from Arsenal than I expected considering their record against top sides. Liverpool were quite tame and surprisingly were in trouble. They may have had goal disallowed and van Dijk should have scored at least one because of Arsena's mistakes but in the end they have to be satisfied with a point here. Torreira was very good today and this was probably best performance from Xhaka that I've seen in Arsenal shirt as both made good challenges and positioned themselves well in many difficult situations. Kolasinac, Mustafi and Leno didn't look convincing and I'm wary that our defense will cost us eventually. But there were many positive signs today and a point against Liverpool is honestly very good result.

          @Castle- Holding played well though and has done for most of the season.
